Pierre F. Lapeyre Jr.Co-Founder and Co-Senior Managing Director, Riverstone Holdings LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 17 Board Members in 17 different organizations across 29 different industries.See Board Relationships54--
Background

		Mr. Pierre F. Lapeyre, Jr., Co-founded Riverstone Holdings LLC in 2000 and serves as its Co-Senior Managing Director. Mr. Lapeyre served as a Managing Director at The Carlyle Group LP and focused on investments in the energy and power sectors. He joined Carlyle on March 1, 2000 and was responsible for sourcing and negotiating investments, as well as post-closing financial structuring and monitoring. He was a General Partner at Magellan Midstream Partners LP since June ... 17, 2003. Mr. Lapeyre served as the Managing Director at Goldman, Sachs & Co in its Global Energy and Power Group. He joined Goldman Sachs in 1986 and spent his 14-year investment banking career focused on energy and power, particularly the midstream, pipeline and oil service sectors. His responsibilities included client coverage and leading the execution of a wide variety of mergers and acquisition, initial public offering, strategic advisory and capital markets financings for clients across all sectors of the industry. While at Goldman Sachs, he served as a Sector Captain for the midstream and pipeline and oil services segments, led coverage of Asian energy companies and was extensively involved in the origination and execution of energy private equity investments. He was responsible for managing Goldman Sachs’ leading franchise in Master Limited Partnerships. He has been a Director of Stallion Oilfield Services Ltd., since June 2006, CDM GP LLC -GP since May 2007. Mr. Lapeyre serves as a Director of Capital C Energy, LLC. He serves on the Boards of Directors of Fieldwood Energy LLC, Atlas Barnett, LLC, Topaz Power Group LLC, Sage Midstream, Niska Gas Storage Canada ULC, Titan, Kinder Morgan, Titan Specialties, Targe Energy LLC, Titan Operating LLC, Three Rivers, Three Rivers III, Dynamic Industries, Amaizeingly Green Products L.P., Green Earth Fuels LLC, Meritage II, SemGroup, CNOR, Quorum Technologies, A. Hak inTANK Services LLC, Gibson Energy, Enduro, Enduro II and Northern Blizzard. He serves as a Non-Executive Director of 4Gas BV. He has been a Director of Centennial Resource Development, Inc. since October 12, 2016. Mr. Lapeyre serves as a Director of Bounty Minerals LLC and Bounty Minerals II LLC. He serves as a Director of Venado, Legend Natural Gas IV, LP and CDM MAX LLC. He serves on the Board of Visitors of the MD Anderson Cancer Center. He serves as a Trustee of The Convent of The Sacred Heart. He served as a Director of EP Energy Corporation until September 3, 2013. He served as a Director of EP Energy LLC since May 2012. He served as a Director of Dresser, Inc., Kinder Morgan Kansas, Inc and Dynamic Energy Service International LLC. He served as a Director of Belden & Blake Corp. at Ward Lake Drilling Inc. since July 2004. Mr. Lapeyre served as a Director of Quorum Business Solutions Inc, CDM Resource Management LLC, Frontier Drilling ASA and Legend Natural Gas LP. He served as a Director of Magellan GP LLC since June 17, 2003. He served as a Director of Cobalt International Energy, Inc., from November 2005 to October 28, 2009. He was a Director of Dynamic Offshore Resources LLC. Mr. Lapeyre served as a Director of Seabulk International, Inc., since September 2002 and Mariner Energy, Inc., since March 2004. He has an M.B.A. from the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill and a B.S. in Finance and Economics from the University of Kentucky.Read Full Background




