P. F. Lapeyre Jr.And Miss HodgesTo Wed in March
Published: November 19, 1989









                    Mrs. Walter James Hodges of Washington has announced the engagement of her daughter, Laurie Lee Hodges, to Pierre Fernand Lapeyre Jr., the son of Mr. and Mrs. Lapeyre of New Orleans. The prospective bride is also the daughter of the late Mr. Hodges. A March wedding is planned.        

                    Miss Hodges, who is employed by Kenney, Kindler, Hunt & Howe, a New York executive-search consulting concern, graduated magna cum laude from Georgetown University and received an M.B.A. degree from New York University.        

                    The prospective bride's father was the president and chief executive of the Fairmac Corporation, a real-estate development concern in Washington. Her mother, Margaret Hodges, is a member of the Board of Regents at Georgetown Univesity, a board member of the National Symphony Orchestra and a member of the Women's Committee of the Smithsonian Institution.        

                    Mr. Lapeyre, an investment banker at Goldman, Sachs & Company in New York, graduated magna cum laude from the University of Kentucky and received an M.B.A. degree from the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.        

                    The prospective bridegroom's father is a vice president with the Hibernia National Bank in New Orleans.        

                    Laurie Hodges (Bachrach)        








 














 













 













 

